Carnitas Caldo

1 tbsp olive oil
1 diced large white onion
1 chayote, skin and core removed, then sliced into matchsticks
8 cloves garlic, thinly sliced
8 c chicken broth
5-6 c carnitas
1-3 roasted serrano peppers
salt & pepper
2 c potato-masa dumplings
2 avocados, diced
1 c fresh baby arugula
lime wedges for garnish

Heat oil in a large stockpot over medium high heat. Add the white onion and chayote, and saute for 5 min until cooked and the onion is translucent. Add garlic and cook for an additional 1-2 min until fragrant. Add the chicken broth, carnitas, and serrano peppers (add 1 at a time to test out the level of heat) and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium-low, cover and simmer for at least 30 min. Season generously with salt and pepper.

Potato-Masa Dumplings
1 c mashed potatoes
1/2 c masa harina
1 egg
1/4 tsp salt

Combine all ingredients in a bowl and stir together until belnded. Use your hands to knead the mixture a few times until smooth. Then pinch off about 1/4 c of the mixture and roll it into a long tube about 1/2" in diameter. Use a knife to slice the tube into small coins, ~1/8" wide. Repeat with the remaining dough to make the dumplings. Cover and refrigerate until ready to use.



Ladle soup into serving bowls, filling them about 1/2 full. Then add in a small handful of potato dumplings, avocados, and fresh cilantro to each bowl. Top each with a large handful of arugula. Server with lime wedges for garnish.

